clinical_particulars.therapeutic_indications: Antithrombin III human is a human antithrombin AT indicated in patients with hereditary antithrombin deficiency for the treatment and prevention of thromboembolism and prevention of peri operative and peri partum thromboembolism

contraindications.pharmacodynamics: Hereditary AT deficiency causes an increased risk of venous thromboembolism VTE During high risk situations such as surgery or trauma or for pregnant women during the peri partum period the risk of development of VTEs as compared to the normal population in these situations is increased by a factor 10 to 50 In hereditary antithrombin deficient patients ATryn restores normalize plasma AT activity levels during peri operative and peri partum periods
